Wash and dry all produce. Peel @ginger{1%thumb}, then mince until you have 2 TBSP. Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the minced ginger and cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add ¾ cups water, @jasmine rice{½%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer until tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until meal is ready.

Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating greens and whites. Core and seed @bell pepper{1}, then cut into thin strips. Drain @pineapple{4%ounce}, reserving juice in a #large bowl{}. Cut any large @cauliflower florets{10%ounce} into bite-size pieces. Roughly chop @peanuts{1%ounce}.

Transfer cauliflower to another large bowl. Sprinkle with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, followed by half the @cornstarch{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat and set aside. Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and cook, tossing, until tender, about ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Add pineapple chunks and scallion whites to pan with bell pepper. Cook until everything begins to brown, about ~{2%minutes} more. Remove from pan and set aside. In the meantime, add @white wine vinegar{5%tsp}, @soy sauce{2%tbsp}, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @sugar{1%tsp}, 2 TBSP water, and remaining ginger and cornstarch to bowl with pineapple juice, stirring until well combined.

Heat @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} in same large pan over medium-high heat. Add cauliflower and cook, tossing occasionally, until browned and nearly cooked through, about ~{3-4%minutes}. Drain oil, then pour sauce into pan and let simmer until it coats cauliflower in a thick glaze, about ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from heat, then return bell pepper mixture to pan and toss to combine.

Divide rice between plates, then top with stir-fry. Garnish with scallion greens and peanuts.